  <title>{pageTitle}</title>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no" />
  <meta
    name="description"
    content="Keep your lawn clean, even, and sharp with professional mowing services from Edwards Landscape Group in Lynchburg, VA."
  />
  <meta
    name="keywords"
    content="lawn mowing lynchburg, weekly mowing service, lawn maintenance VA, grass cutting"
  />
  <link id="favicon" rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/assets/favicon.ico" />
  <link
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lato:300,400,700&display=swap"
    rel="stylesheet"
  />
  <link
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Poppins:300,400,500,600,700,800,900"
    rel="stylesheet"
  />
  <link
    rel="stylesheet"
    href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css"
  />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/animate.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/owl.carousel.min.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/owl.theme.default.min.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/magnific-popup.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/ionicons.min.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/flaticon.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/icomoon.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <TopBar />

  <Navigation />
  <main class="service-page service-page--compact">
    <section
      class="service-hero service-hero--trugreen service-hero--compact"
      style="background-image: url('/public/assets/Mowing/Mowing7.jpg');"
    >
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-lg-9 col-xl-7 hero-content-block">
            <h1 class="mb-2">Lawn Mowing</h1>
            <p class="mb-4 lead">
              Our professional lawn mowing services keep your property looking clean and well-maintained
              throughout the growing season. We provide consistent, reliable service so you never have to
              worry about your lawn’s appearance.
            </p>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Get a Free Quote</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">What’s included with Lawn Mowing</h2>
        <div class="matrix-grid">
          <div class="matrix-card">
            <h3>Proper mowing height</h3>
            <p>
              We adjust the mowing height to match the season and your grass type, keeping turf
              thicker, greener, and more resilient between visits.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="matrix-card">
            <h3>Precision edging</h3>
            <p>
              Clean, sharp edges along sidewalks, driveways, and beds give your lawn that freshly
              manicured look that stands out in the neighborhood.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="matrix-card">
            <h3>Surface cleanup</h3>
            <p>
              We blow off grass clippings from patios, walkways, and driveways so your property
              looks finished, not just cut.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="matrix-card">
            <h3>Reliable scheduling</h3>
            <p>
              Weekly service keeps growth in check, with timing tailored to your
              lawn’s needs so it always looks ready for guests.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Why Lawn Mowing Matters</h2>
        <ul class="bullet-list">
          <li>Improves curb appeal with a fresh, consistently manicured appearance.</li>
          <li>Encourages healthier grass growth by keeping blades at the right height.</li>
          <li>Helps reduce weed pressure by maintaining a dense, vigorous turf canopy.</li>
          <li>Saves you time each week while keeping the lawn guest-ready year-round.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <div
          class="service-visual"
          style="--service-accent-start: #f1f9f6; --service-accent-end: #d7f0e5; --service-accent-badge: #2f7d59;"
        >
          <div class="row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-lg-6 mb-4 mb-lg-0">
              <span class="service-visual__eyebrow">Fresh Cut</span>
              <h2 class="mb-3">Crisp stripes and a clean finish</h2>
              <p>
                Regular mowing keeps your lawn looking polished, reduces stress on the turf, and
                creates the neat, uniform appearance homeowners love.
              </p>
              <ul class="pill-list">
                <li class="pill">Consistent schedule</li>
                <li class="pill">Sharp edging</li>
                <li class="pill">Clean cleanup</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
              <img
                class="service-visual__image"
                src="/public/assets/Mowing/Mowing8.jpg"
                alt="Freshly mowed lawn with crisp striping"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Benefits of Lawn Mowing in Lynchburg, VA</h2>
        <div class="matrix-grid">
          <div class="matrix-card">
            <h3>Consistent curb appeal</h3>
            <p>Weekly mowing keeps your lawn looking clean, even, and professional throughout the growing season.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="matrix-card">
            <h3>Healthier turf density</h3>
            <p>Proper mowing height encourages thicker grass, which helps crowd out weeds and supports long-term lawn health.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="matrix-card">
            <h3>Safer, usable outdoor space</h3>
            <p>Regular mowing reduces pests, hides fewer hazards, and keeps your yard comfortable for family use.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="service-accordion">
          <details open>
            <summary>How often should my lawn be mowed?</summary>
            <p>
            Most lawns do best with weekly mowing during peak growth. During slower growth, bi-weekly service may be enough.
            We can recommend a schedule based on your grass type, shade, and how you want it to look.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do you bag clippings or mulch them?</summary>
            <p>
            In many cases we mulch clippings because it returns nutrients to the soil. If your lawn is overgrown or you prefer bagging,
            we can discuss options based on your property and the time of year.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Will mowing help with weeds?</summary>
            <p>
            Consistent mowing helps keep your lawn thicker and healthier, which can reduce space for weeds to establish.
            Weed issues may still require targeted treatment depending on the type and severity.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do you mow in the rain?</summary>
            <p>
            We avoid mowing saturated lawns to prevent ruts and turf damage. If weather delays service, we’ll return as soon as conditions allow.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>How short do you cut the grass?</summary>
            <p>
            We aim for a healthy height based on the season. Cutting too short can stress the lawn, cause yellowing, and invite weeds.
            We adjust height to support long-term health and appearance.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Can you mow around landscaping, playsets, and obstacles?</summary>
            <p>
            Yes. We mow carefully around beds, trees, playsets, and common obstacles. If an area requires special handling, let us know during the quote.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do you offer one-time mowing?</summary>
            <p>
            Yes, one-time mowing may be available depending on schedule and property conditions. Most customers choose recurring service for the best results.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Will you edge every visit?</summary>
            <p>
            Edging is commonly included to keep the lawn looking crisp. Exact frequency can depend on growth and the service plan you choose.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <RelatedServiceBlogs serviceType="mowing" heading="Related Lawn Care Articles" />
  </main>

  <Footer />

  <div id="ftco-loader" class="show fullscreen">
    <svg class="circular" width="48px" height="48px">
      <circle class="path-bg" cx="24" cy="24" r="22" fill="none" stroke-width="4" stroke="#eeeeee"
      ></circle>
      <circle
        class="path"
        cx="24"
        cy="24"
        r="22"
        fill="none"
        stroke-width="4"
        stroke-miterlimit="10"
        stroke="#F96D00"></circle>
    </svg>
  </div>

